author: @imraff
text: the reason that halite_dict[position] = halite_amount was erroring is because you were trying to use a dict as a key in another dict, that doesn't work because keys have to be hashable and generally only immutable objects can be hashed, trying to pass position the frozenset(position_dict[direction]) turns it into an non-iterable object... Programming is fun -.-

author: @BluEagl
text: The Position class implements __eq__, which discards __hash__ . I just added to the class: __hash__ = object.__hash__  It seemed to work, but have not done any real testing of it.

author: @Alex4n3r
text: Did this yesterday in one hour. The dict only works because directions are characters whereas positions are tuples which are not hashable by python. This solution didn't account for the cost of movement and time not used for collecting. Daniel Kukila is currently on place 12! WOW!
